    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a little water in a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>peanut butter</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> ground cumin</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>your <strong>lime</strong> and mix until fully combined</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Gradually whisk in 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[5 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, a little at a time, until a smooth, thick sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>peanut sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion is slightly softened, reduce the heat to low</p><p>Add your<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> ground paprika </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), stir it all together and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato spiced rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, cut a large piece of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 sheet of paper</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Do this in batches!)</p><p>Add your<strong> basa fillet[s]</strong> to the middle of the foil</p><p>Pour the <strong>peanut sauce </strong>evenly over the <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Scrunch the edges of the foil together around the fish to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Add the parcel[s]<strong> </strong>to a baking tray[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the basa is cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> West African-style peanut basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is in the oven, trim your<strong> green beans</strong> and chop in half, then add the<strong> chopped beans </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the beans to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the beans are tender</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/west-african-style-peanut-basa-with-tomato-spiced-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>West African-style peanut basa</strong> with the <strong>spiced tomato rice</strong> and<strong> green beans </strong>to the side</p><p>Spoon the <strong>remaining peanut sauce</strong> from the parcel over the basa and sprinkle with your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
